Cold Oven Cake
  --B. Dylan Hollis

1 c butter or margarine at room temp
1/2 c shortening: Crisco/Lard (Or omit, and simply use 1 & 1/2 c of butter) at room temp
3 c white sugar
3 c sifted ap flour
1/2 tsp baking powder
1 c milk at room temp
5 eggs at room temp
1 tsp vanilla 
1 tsp coconut extract

In a large bowl, cream together butter, shortening, and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time. Sift together flour and baking powder in a separate bowl. Fold in flour mixture & milk to the butter mixture, alternating in small portions. Stir in extracts. Turn into a buttered & floured 10" tube/bundt pan, or similarly sized vessel Place in a cold oven, setting temperature to 350F and bake for ~ 1 hr & 15 min. Cool cake in pan for 5 min, then invert onto a cooling rack. Cool completely before slicing.


Notes: probably want to add 1/2 tsp salt
